{"word":"ἄγραυλος","slug":"ἄγραυλος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄγραυλος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἀγρός αὐλή</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>dwelling in the field</i>, of shepherds, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; <el>ἄγρ. ἀνήρ</el> <i>a boor</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of oxen, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>of things, <i>rural, rustic</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}